sub_title: Secretaris Medisch Ethische Toetsingscommissie (METC) - Amsterdam UMC
summary: Innovation-driven enthusiastic cardiovascular scientist with strong background in physiology, immunology, translational medicine and tissue engineering. Successfully set-up an engineered heart tissue test system and optimized scientific protein exchange protocols. Strong university teaching skills, biomedical network and communication skills. Highly organized team-player with a clear and positive approach to problem solving. Areas of expertise include: research design and development, scientific writing, drug testing, presenting at scientific meetings, critical and analytical thinking.

I focus on molecular alterations and treatment targets for hypertrophic cardiomyopathy in human engineered heart tissue. Engineered heart tissue allows to study contractile function longitudinally in human tissue and to investigate early mutation-induced perturbations and test drug therapies. My current studies provide a proof-of-concept that diabetes medication (sodium-glucose cotransporter 2 inhibitors like empagliflozin, canagliflozin and dapagliflozin) restores impaired relaxation in engineered heart tissue with hypertrophic cardiomyopathy mutations. Since I first started working with cardiac muscle, I have been fascinated by the multiple mechanisms that affect muscle contractility in health and disease.
